==Tage Kitabatakeshi shi Jōkan (Kitabatake clan`s residence and castle)== Kitabatakeshi Yakata was fortified residence of the Tage [[Kitabatake clan]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.info.city.tsu.mie.jp/www/contents/1001000011242/index.html |title=続日本100名城 |publisher=日本城郭協会|language=Japanese|accessdate=25 July 2019}}</ref> Now Kitabatake Shrine is on site. But the garden made by Kitabatake clan is still remains.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tsukanko.jp/spot/183/ |title=北畠氏館跡庭園|publisher=津市観光協会|language=Japanese|accessdate=25 July 2019}}</ref> Also Kitabatake clan built Kiriyama Castle on the mountain behind Kitabatakeshi Yakata( Kiriyama castle was used in emergencies.).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kojodan.jp/castle/1255/ |title=北畠氏館跡|publisher=攻城団|language=Japanese|accessdate=25 July 2019}}</ref>Kiriyama Castle is now only ruins with some eathen walls and dry moat.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://shirobito.jp/castle/1719 |title=霧山城 |publisher=城びと|language=Japanese|accessdate=25 July 2019}}</ref>
